4.11	NPR_controversies	NPR controversies	NPR, formerly National Public Radio, is a privately and publicly funded non-profit membership media organization that serves as a national syndicator to 797 public radio stations in the United States of America. Various allegations of bias, both from conservative and liberal sources, and controversies have arisen throughout NPR's history.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/National_Public_Radio_logo.svg/163px-National_Public_Radio_logo.svg.png
